caption: I just ordered my food on seamless and I'm waiting to write the review there too but OMG I love this place already. I love Vietnamese food and this is my favorite place hands down. I ordered the pho bo em and mien ga, spring rolls, aloe its me, avocado, mango + passion smoothie. EVERYTHING IS DELICIOUS PERIOD!!! I will absolutely order again in the future. Also, the woman who delivered my food is so sweet I wish I asked her for her name she made my day and I'm glad she made it safe driving in this rain <3 Thank you so much! Please support this business they are wonderful!
High quality and extremely tasty food for an amazing price. Ordered for delivery and everyone was super nice and friendly !!
Loved the sandwich and the pho! Very tasty

have only ordered delivery from Em and all of the drivers are always awesome! i'm so glad to see that Pat doesn't have to handle all of the orders anymore (thank you for always delivering to my window) cause i know the delivery radius can be quite troublesome at times. sandwiches are always on point and I love the vegan spring rolls; especially the sauce that comes with it. i hope minced bbq pork gets added to the menu cause that's what got me into banh mi in the first place, thank you for bringing authentic viet to south bk! i also forgot to mention that the drinks are all fantastic as well. PLEASE TRY THIS PLACE.
Absolutely in love with this place! Remember to call in to order pick up to support your local business. Those apps take a huge cut.

I am waiting for the order in that place through UberEats 2 hours. And after 2 hours of waiting they canceled the order because they are closing! Are you really? I am waited for two hours! Hoooow? The baddest order experience in my life. Shame!
It’s very good🤠
I had ordered the banh mi bo. It was aromic and tasted amazing. The combination of the pickled vegetables and the beef was jumping in my mouth and it was bursting with flavors. Will eat here again!

Their banh mi sandwiches taste very authentic and the bread they use is really fresh, crisp out the outside and soft inside.  Vietnamese iced coffee is out of this world. Also had the cha gio rolls, very good!
Business close on Tuesday. Delivery available!
Delicious pho. The spare rib add on is worth getting - super tender and tasty.
excellent Vietnamese restaurant, friendly staff.

Ate here with a friend who's Vietnamese. He was impressed with the little plastic stools that reminded him of home. I was impressed with their vegetarian broth. I recommend to anyone trying to hit up a good spot on a cold day.

(Translated by Google) Locomotive is unpalatable than other Vietnamese restaurants. The advantage is that there is no MSG, the Vietnamese bread is not crisp enough, not refreshing enough, and there are not enough shredded carrots, which is not as good as the Qingna I have eaten at 7th Avenue.  (Original) 火车头比其他越南餐厅难吃，好处是没有味精，越南面包不够脆，不够清爽，萝卜丝不够多，比不上我在7大道吃过的清娜
yummy food and good services but limited menu. wish more choice on menu
2 choices of soup noodle. not many choices like a regular pho restaurant. I think their smoothies could be good. they claim to use real fruits not powder.

Sandwiches looks very tasty and heavy. But I’m not enjoy to meat inside. But it’s totally good place . Wanna try noodles I think this the favorite . Thx for service in pay pkway. Sometimes we need something special than just regular food and you guys very helping to us to taste this piece of Vietnamese food. I’m enjoying to the place . very clean customer service five stars , clear English welcome face , and girl on the front desk will you help me to toys in a sandwich from menú and explain to me what kind of meat is going to Show me all positions and I did my choice I got the Deluxe  something

Sandwiches were excellent along with the smoothies and unique drinks that are served here. This mom and pop eatery is great for a small family unit to enjoy right outside or order out. Their small added touches to traditional appetizers make them such a landmark for EM. The quality, freshness, and richness of the food and drink makes the price justified.
Great family owned place, amazing service, awesome food love the place

Glad to find a Vietnamese restaurant that I am, at the very least, decently satisfied with...I think I got more than what I anticipated because I am MORE than satisfied with this place. Beyond happy to finally find a place that serves Southern Vietnamese Pho. Honestly, best Pho I’ve ever had. Flavors are excellent and exciting even for the picky eaters in my household. I order from this place whenever I’m feeling sick and in need of a nice chicken soup, or whenever I am simply in the mood for a nice big bowl of Pho. Prices are very reasonable, you get a ton of delicious pho for what you pay for. More than worth it in my opinion. The drinks are also delicious, though a bit pricey for the size. Have had some of the rolls as well. I’ve tried quite a few items on their menu and everything is A+ for me. Would eat from here every day if I could.

My new favorite Vietnamese place. I'm glad I read about it somewhere online and went there to try. The pho with 24 hr beef broth is to die for.  Pork belly with rice is also delicious. They even passed the taste test from my dad, which is equivalent to one Micheline star.I only wish they have chilly garlic sauce available. The ladies who work there are always very pleasant.

Have not had Vietnamese food in months due to the quarantine and this was a great pick. The banh mi was delicious, bread was light and crusty, great ratio of meat to pickled veg and exactly the right spice level for my taste buds. Meats tasted like they were a cut above your average joint. They have direct online ordering (hate predatory Seamless/GrubHub) anddo curbside pick up. There was a small mix up with our order and the owner, Patrick, was super accomodating and even hooked us up with an order of spring rolls to make up for it. We scarfed our sandwiches and iced coffee in the car, but looking forward to eating the rest of our order when we get home.

Pho Bo Em with the $8 short rib addition is definitely worth it. Nice serving of short rib, very well cooked and super tender. Takeout container for the noodle soup is nicer than others and very convenient. Smoothies are also very good
I get delivery from here all the time and the food is great. I'm not sure what the delivery guy's name is but he is so friendly and gives good service every time I order.
They serve food with passions

This is our second time ordering from there since the quarantine but I fully intend to be a lifetime regular. I love their pho, with the passion of a thunder strike I love their pho. My wife had a passionate affair with the Bahn Mi Dac Biet tonight and I’m not even mad. The summer rolls are so refreshing. They are a joyful smile with every bite. I do the happy boy food dance eating from here, I really do.
Came last week - ordered the Pho a bit pricey for the neighborhood- on point consistantly made... not a place for a sit down ...food is highly recommended

I have been there like 3 times before but today I made the first order for delivery (thanks quarantine) and OMG that was delicious! Delivery person was nice and tidy, wearing gloves and face mask, he was very polite and Pho was great! I wish I could find words for this! Meat and broth was so delicious and vegetables were very fresh.
Not worth the price. Manhattan prices for no reason. There are better pho places in the area
Amazing food. I love the soups and nice staff
Good but prices are little high for a bowl of pho.
The broth for the beef pho was delicious, i just wish I had more noodles because I wanted more. Definitely recommend it!

I would of given this place 4 stars if the service was better. The pho was excellent, the broth was so flavorful, but the customer service needs some improvement. We had to ask for water refills twice and the servers never came over to see if we needed anything the whole time.
I love these guys. Great banh mis and amazing pho. Extremely original and always satisfying.
great food and service but small place. price to portion ratio is a bit iffy but it's the best pho in bensonhurst for sure.

This restaurant is ok.  I wouldn’t say good. — Cons: We were given wooden rewashed chopsticks. The tea was served warm, not hot. Deceiving Online pictures of loaded up noodle broth dishes,,, we were served mainly broth. Atmosphere felt cold. Pros: Free tea, with refills. The Beef in the broth was very tender. The service was ok, but felt inexperienced.
The Pho was amazing here. We will come back often. Thank You
(Translated by Google) Less place, food and price are not relative  (Original) 地方少，食物及價錢不相對

It was small yet the pho was superb, nice taste and well prepared. I just hope they would put may be some more beef meat balls in there in their house special pho. Price wise it is decent. Food was prepared and given on timely manner. I love it. I was surprised why it is not that crowded or may be because it is in Brooklyn??? Anyways people, please give a try.
Amazing food! We went to Em’s and had the Wonton Soup, pork dumplings and egg rolls. Everything tasted fresh! We will be back!
Best pho
The pho ga was delicious!
The food is tasty BUT they need to increase the quantity. By spending $12 for a bowl of Pho I am still hungry. I mean noodle is cheap and they need to justify the $12 tag.  I may not go back again.

I ordered the shredded chicken pho and spring rolls for delivery. Everything was delicious and nicely packed. The broth was very flavorful. They were a little skimpy with the meat and generous with the noodles and veggies. Everything was fresh and delicious. I will be eating from here again.
Food is not bad but their customers service was ridiculous
Their Menu is so cute and simple to order from! Food is great and drinks are delicious as well. Quick service too!

Soups and spring rolls were awesome! The soups does not have too much MSG in it which is very hard to find among all other ones that adds MSG in like crazy and make my mouth feels like dessert. Spring rolls were crispy and yummy, packed with veggie and the vinegar sauce was super tasty. I will bring my parents in next time.

Their pho was slightly different from the usual pho at other viet restaurants. The broth was very refreshing and flavorful. Despite their menu being smaller than the usually viet  restaurant, the selections were still plenty. They have sandwiches here too and an interesting smoothies menu. I got their beef noodle soup and the Aloe It's Me drink 0w0. The pho was very good and the drink had chia seeds and aloe chunks in it, which I really liked. My friends got the same thing but different drinks: the Summer of 69 and the pineapple Express. Both were very good too.
good place for grouping, very instagrammable
The beef pho was great! Place is clean and upbeat!
Not horrible. But the overusage of vegetables and the small portions mixed with high prices leaves you rather unsatisfied.

Actually sat down to enjoy my meal! Its cozy here, with limited seating.  The first time I was here, i had ordered takeout. But nothing beats seating in the restaurant to enjoy their food. 😁  Staff was friendly and patient. So far one of the better coffee served is here! Love that their menu is small, but enough.  Their smoothies are outta this world... had Mango tango 2x already as take out.  Had take out Banh Mi Nem for later snack.😁 Loved the Banh mi stuffing... meh on the bread.
Very good service. Pho is light and flavorful. Their smoothies are the best! Very fresh and yummy
Excellent customer service  Nice place.  Delicious food. 😋

Yammy sandwiches,very tasty lemonade and smoothies... haven't tried noodles yet. Staff was friendly and service was excellent. It's a small pace, not a big restaurant, but very beautiful interior. I loved the way, how they serve food - sandwiches were in some kind of baskets, smoothies in a beautiful glasses. I ENJOYED THIS PLACE! 5STAR OF COURSE!
So good Noodle soups!100%
BEST PHO EVER!!!! Smoothies are really good also!
I've had the beef broth pho for take out but was not impressed. Decided to give it another chance and was pleasantly surprised.  The signature and beef bowls both joined the clean bowl club!
Not much space to sit, but food is great.
Fresh to order sandwiches... excellent seasoning... very tasteful... and the soups are the bomb... the bomb is a great thing... jijijiji...

It's a different kind of vietnamese restaurant. If you don't have chives and cilantro, don't get this. My kids wouldn't eat this, but like the traditional Vietnamese places. The soup is very flavorful and I personally enjoyed the noodles. The restaurant is very small, so don't expect to come here with a large party. The menu is extremely small, so honestly, I don't think I would order anything else if they expanded the menu. The other stuff you can get at another viet restaurant. Their soup noodles are unique and if you come here, you should come for the soup noodles.

(Translated by Google) The shop is small, the stuff is expensive, the beef noodles are only five slices of beef, and the price is twice that of an authentic Vietnamese shop. !! !!  (Original) 店很小、東西很貴、牛肉麵只有五片牛肉、而且價格是正宗越南店的兩倍、無語、！！！
great service!!! tasty food!
More noodles in serving :)

Good and filling, got the pho and added the short rib which was a nice big chunk. Also had the marinated pork app which I've never had before. The service was good and since we were the only ones there for an early dinner very attentive. P. S. Infused water is served!

(Translated by Google) Agent to you and was not there last month. I went to school and do not know what you know in the camp.  (Original) Агент к тебе и не было в прошлом месяце начну. Ушла в школу не знаю что ты знаешь во лагерь.

Prior to my experience today, I would have given them a 5-star. Tonight, I placed an order on their website at 7:20pm (I even have a Revel email that has the timestamp and the estimated delivery time of 8:05pm). Came 8:15pm, my order was still not here, so I called them and explained the issue, only to be told that it was arriving “soon”. Another 15 minutes has gone by, so I called again and told them that I had been waiting for more than an hour. The response I got was that I placed my order at 8:03pm and that it would take another 10 minutes for my order to come with no apologies. At 8:43pm, finally the order arrived with everything spilled in the bag...
More expensive than your typical Vietnamese restaurants, but also much higher quality Pho. Also excellent service since it is a small shop.
Soups are authentic and delicious, just like mom makes!
Amazing noodles!! tasted just like home cooking!
Great place! The owner was very friendly! And great food!

Great cozy place for vietnamese food. The place has a great atmosphere. I went here on a weekend with my bf and it was packed. People kept coming in and had to wait. A guy ( I'm guessing was the owner) welcomed us and explained a few of the food options since it was our 1st time there. He was very nice and friendly. The food was great. It was a bit pricey but worth it. I would come here again.
Decent pho but for $12 its too expensive

VIETNAM 🇻🇳 Eat the World NYC review: Back in April, we wrote about a lovely new Vietnamese restaurant on 86th Street in Brooklyn that opened rather quietly and offered a succinct menu of well-made dishes. It had an edge to it that was distinct from most of the country's noodle soups offered in New York City. Fast forward to December and it is with happiness we can report that the hu tieu is still without equal, and the noodles are as good as ever. We also finally tried the pho ga, a chicken soup that is modified from the recipe of the chef's mother. It is good too, and offers a good switch so you do not have to order the same thing every time, although each is worth of that. The menu is still focused on dishes that the kitchen does well, and that is a good sign. ° New also to our post is the cha gio, fried spring rolls we ordered this time instead of the nem nuong rolls. All of the past and new info is updated on our page from April so if you missed that check it out now. Bensonhurst is an important place for Vietnamese in the city, home to what we think are the three strongest restaurants.

Great new local vietnamese place with an enthusiastic owner.  They make it easy by focusing on a few dishes that taste great, rather than overwhelming the customer with 100 options like some places do. Great fruit smoothies!!!
Taste good but expensive.
Amazing food! Staff were so friendly. We need more restaurants like this, they really put hard work in the flavoring of their food.  My new viet spot and worth the drive.
Been coming  here at least once a month since opening. Still the best tasting soup in my life. Chicken or Pork FTW! Beef is pretty good too. The sammies could be better.
Different but is it worth the price? I don't think so.

Great place to get some tasty pho. The staff here is friendly and attentive. Some items on here are pricier than your normal pho places. Their broth that they used for their pho is quite good, doesn't seem like they used a lot of MSG. The Vietnamese ice coffee was amazing.
This place is my favorite pho restaurant Food is always great and staff is always very friendly.
Great quality food at a quality price

Tastes different from most places. Doesn't seem like a heavy use of msg. I think that may be why there seems to be something missing from the broth. The chicken broth is good if you want something plain and simple. There's a dip that goes with the chicken and that adds a lot to the flavor.

I love the food here, it's authentic and delicious! This place is cozy with a friendly staff and the best pho in Brooklyn. They have a great selection of fresh drinks and a beef sandwich to die for. If you are in the area or just want to try some authebaut vietnamVie pho definitely stop by this place.
Best Viet food in NYC

(Translated by Google) When tasting Vietnamese iced coffee, the taste of the coffee already feels rich and smooth. When tasting the coffee cake, the strong aroma of coffee and the light aroma of the cake, the taste is delicate and smooth.  (Original) 品尝越南冰咖啡时，入口己经感觉咖啡的香浓细腻润滑。品尝咖啡蛋糕时，咖啡的浓香与蛋糕淡淡的香，口感细腻且润滑。

It's a very relaxing environment, and very cozy to sit in. The music isn't too loud, and it feels just right. The staff is friendly, and won't hesitate to answer any questions. I always order the chicken noodles because that is my ULTIMATE FAVE. I often order it as the sauce really spikes up my hunger level and makes me want to eat more. For drinks, I often order the viet ice coffee, but I'm definitely going to try out more smoothies and drinks soon!
Ok pho. Small hole in the wall.
Best viet. Not your usual flavor

My family discovered this place via a NY Times food review. The soup base is great and all the meat are of quality. We ordered spring rolls and pho 🍲. The spring rolls come out hot and crunchy. The pho has a good portion of meat vs noodles. This quaint noodle shop will be on our regular list to go for family dinner.
My favorite place in all of Brooklyn to eat from
Good addition to the neighborhood.  Clean and quick.  Excellent drinks and food.
Good foods
Great service
3.5 stars. Better than your average NYC Vietnamese food but not special enough for me to hurry back given their small menu. Salty plum drink was good.

New Viet joint around 86th and 16th ave. They're regular pork and shrimp with noodles is so good. They give you a piece of meat with the bone that falls right off which is so tender and juicy. It's a must go

Em is more known for its Banh Mi and it's Sinh to (shakes). My friend and I wanted to try the soups done it was a balmy day.  I ordered the Hu Tieu. Not a lot of Vietnamese restaurant offer this type of soup. Pork bone broth based soup rather than the beef broth based Pho. The noodle soup has a pork rib, shrimp and fish balls. The taste isn't isn't extra ordinary from what my family makes. It's missing an aromatic taste.  The pho my friend ordered has a overly aromatic taste that it goes the sense of salty savory from the Pho. There is only one type of Pho so if your looking for the beef round that cooks in the broth, try another restaurant.  The noodle soup is a bit expensive compared to other Vietnamese restaurants ($12-14l. Vietnamese noodle soups don't have the taste intracacies like Ramen to charge what Em charges.  Overall, Em is a nice restaurant for quick eats like Banh mi. Pass soon the noodle soups.
Menu is a little lacking

Recently opened, Em serve authentic vietnamese casual quick street foods in a small , modern, cute place on 86st and 17th ave . My friends and I came on a Sunday night, no wait time. We had the goi cuon, hu tieu, and banh mi. For drinks, we had the viet ice coffee, avocado and coconut smoothies. We'll definitely come again, thanks for opening lol
Love it! I suggest the beef bahn mi.
Used to be better.  But now the beef pho was overpriced and for the viet sandwich the bread was stale.

I’ve been looking for a great bowl of pho since moving here from the West Coast three years ago and I’ve finally found it. The broth hits all the right spice notes and coats your throat in sticky collagen, the noodles are served perfectly chewy, and the toppings are all fresh. It’s not too salty, not too sweet, not too bland, it tastes like pho should taste.
Authentic and deliscious. The pho broth is on point and the coconut smoothie is so fresh. Definite must go.
Great noodle. I like to pork noodle

Wow just discovered this place and I already love it. It's small menu and shop but what they do have, they make it well. I didn't try the banh mi but I did have the beef pho with short rib and it was delicious. Much closer to a homemade broth and so much better than the usual stuff you get on 8 Ave or 86 st under the train. You can tell how good pho is by the broth and this one had a clean, refreshing flavor but with lots of body. The beef pho didn't have tendon or tripe but that's ok with me. I also got a limeade drink and watermelon smoothie and both were also very refreshing. Came here on a Saturday 6pm and it wasn't that busy but lots of locals. Definitely worth a visit or even a short trip if you're craving good pho.

It’s a bit hard to rate this restaurant so my rating tends to be more neutral. I like the fact that they don’t use MSG in their cooking and the taste is close to homemade style which is different from all other well established Vietnamese restaurants I have been too. The restaurant is cute and clean but rather tiny. Their menu seems to have more juice/Smoothie options than noodles and banh mi or other Vietnamese food which looks more like a juicy bar to me. When I was there the other day, the lady who made juice behind counter had been busy using the blender the whole time when I was having lunch which made the tiny restaurant rather noisy.
This place is amazing.  They have a new Banh mi made with warm beef stewed in their pho broth... it was one of the best things I’ve ever eaten.  Be back soon to try it with egg.

very friendly staffs and comfortable environment. place is very clean. Nothing compare to the typical vietnamese restaurant around the area. As they stated in their menu Zero MSG added.The soup is well broth and absolutely not thrist you out for hours after consuming. Highly recommended this place. Some reviewer state that there are not enough choices on the menu in which they disliked but I found this to be the positive side. I totally agreed with the owner that quality is more important.
Very knowledgeable staff. Small place but well kept..
Small menu but really good food!
Just going for the sandwiches alone is worth it

Great lunch spot.  We tried the Bahn Mi Op Sa and Bahn Mi Bacon Egg and Cheese.  These were delicious; the fried egg adds a lot to the Bahn Mi, it will not disappoint.  Also go for the mango tango, very good drink.
Delicious!!! Spring rolls w the lettuce is the best I have so far in NYC ! Seafood Noodle soup is just wakening for the taste buds!

Stopped by for lunch with the family at this newly opened Viet restaurant. The menu is limited to 2 types of pho and 4 different sandwiches.  We ordered both types of pho and were pleasantly surprised.  The soup from the pork pho had a good depth of flavor.  Their iced coffee is tasty with a sweet bold finish.  Even though it might be pre-made.

This place looks very clean and inviting. I was hoping that this place would be different from all the Banh Mi places in NY. Unfortunately it is not. If the owner of the restaurant looked up what Banh Mi means in Vietnamese they would see that it's pointing to BREAD. Not sure how it started in NY but a good Banh Mi starts with the bread and it has to be crispy on the outside and soft and airy on the inside. Instead we got a dense bread here in NY. The ingredients inside are typical but fresh which I commend this place for. The ice coffee is good, I think I would go there more for their coffee than the Banh Mi.  Nice Try...
Pretty good noodles, the banh mi was good too. Drinks were great but pretty pricey.
Good food and friendly staff!

They have the best smoothies in town! Also, I love their spring roll, not too oily and the stuff taste fresh. I had the Pho Ga and like the fact the broth is not over seasoned. I'll definitely go back and try their other pho.
It is a nice pho spot for the local area. The banh mi is nice fusion twist. Price  is not too bad.
Tasty food, nice staff and relaxing environment. Welcome addition to Bensonhurst.
The service is good and the food(Vietnamese noodles and sandwich) is ok.
Soft opening week, delicious food.
The place was pretty good but didn’t get 5 stars because they only had the pork soup left by the time I got there. They ran out of the Bahn Mi and the other flavor soups.
This was great. Food was great, staff was friendly and everything was awesome. Highly recommend
All the option tastes great and fresh. I especially like the banh mi. It has the authentic tastes I had when I was in Vietnam.

The Chicken noodle is more like the Malaysian style. The Vietnamese Hamburger is not bad too. Price is a little higher than others. There is only two noodles and 4 sandwich selection, not good enough. Hope this place will last at least a year!

What a pleasant surprise! Walked by this place last week and was told it was still their soft opening. Wife & I decided to give it a shot and ordered a pho and a bah mi sandwich. WOW, what a pleasant surprise. Perhaps the BEST vietnamese food in Brooklyn!!! We have been looking for a great place like this to go to on a regular basis and I'm glad to say, WE'VE FOUND IT!!!!
